# 🦾 Joystick-Controlled Servo Arm

A dual-axis robotic arm controlled in real time using two joysticks and an Arduino. Each joystick axis maps to a servo motor, letting you move the arm freely along the X and Y axes. The movement of the arm is tracked in real time on the serial monitor in the arduino IDE. 



---

## 📋 How It Works

Two analog joysticks send signals to the Arduino via analog pins. The Arduino reads each joystick's position (0–1023), maps that value to a servo angle (0°–180°), and writes the angle to the corresponding servo motor — all in a continuous loop with a 500ms delay between updates.

| Joystick Axis | Analog Pin | Servo Pin | Controls |
|---|---|---|---|
| X-axis | A3 | Pin 6 | Horizontal rotation |
| Y-axis | A2 | Pin 2 | Vertical tilt |

---

## 🛒 Components

- Arduino (Uno or compatible)
- 2× Servo motors
- 2× Analog joystick modules
- Jumper wires
- Breadboard
- USB cable (for power & serial monitor)

---

## 🔌 Wiring

```
Joystick X-axis  →  Arduino A3
Joystick Y-axis  →  Arduino A2
Servo X signal   →  Arduino Pin 6
Servo Y signal   →  Arduino Pin 2
```

Both servos and joysticks share `5V` and `GND` from the Arduino.

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

1. **Clone this repo**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/YOUR-REPO.git
   ```

2. **Open the sketch** — Open `JoystickServoController.ino` in the [Arduino IDE](https://www.arduino.cc/en/software).

3. **Install the Servo library** — Go to **Sketch → Include Library → Manage Libraries**, search for `Servo`, and install it.

4. **Wire up the components** following the wiring diagram above.

5. **Upload the sketch** to your Arduino and open the Serial Monitor at **9600 baud** to watch live position values.

---

## 💻 Code Overview

```cpp
int JoyX = analogRead(joyvalX);       // Read joystick X position (0–1023)
posX = map(JoyX, 0, 1023, 0, 180);   // Convert to servo angle (0°–180°)
servoX.write(posX);                   // Move servo to that angle
```

The same logic applies to the Y-axis. Serial output lets you monitor both axes in real time.

